HEADWORD: Lum
<hw>Lum</hw> <pr>(l⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W.
<ets>llumon</ets> chimney, <ets>llum</ets> that shoots up or ends in a
point.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A chimney.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ventilating chimney over the shaft of a
mine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A woody valley; also, a deep pool.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumachella</ent>⟦br⟧
